{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/manifests/alain-martin-richard-at-ultimatum-festival-1985-05-03.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"en":["Alain-Martin Richard at Ultimatum Festival 1985-05-03"]},"homepage":[{"id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985","type":"Text","label":{"en":["Alain-Martin Richard at Ultimatum Festival 1985-05-03"]},"format":"text/html"}],"metadata":[{"label":{"en":["Description"]},"value":{"en":["The following is a transcription of the Alain-Martin Richard set at Ultimatum, Friday, May 3rd, 1985 at the Foufounes Electriques. Richard is a multidisciplinary artist, editor and critic from Quebec, Canada, active since the late 70s, touring and presenting at festivals and events across North America, Europe and Japan. Previously, he was a member of the defunct international collective The Nomads and of INTER/Le Lieu from Quebec City. More recently, he has been involved with the collective Les Causes Perdues and Folie/Culture, having co-created the poetic game, \"Lʹatopie textutelle est une cause qui se perd\". He co-edited Performance in/au Canada 1970-1990 with Clive Robertson, the book Territoires Nomades and various catalogues and publications on art and performance. His experimental practice questions the social and the everyday, postmodernism, space and identity.\n"]}},{"label":{"en":["Language"]},"value":{"en":["English"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/alain_martin_richard_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_03/canvas/4","type":"Canvas","duration":0,"annotations":[{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/manifests/alain_martin_richard_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_03-canvas4-1","type":"AnnotationPage","label":{"en":["Default"]},"items":[{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://spokenweb.github.